(Practice: HTTP Performance & Persistence, DNS Resolution Mechanics, Network Performance Metrics) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Question 1) Tj
T*
(In a DNS resolution process using iterative queries, if a local DNS server needs to) Tj
T*
(resolve a hostname and the mapping is not in its cache, it contacts a Root server, then) Tj
T*
(a TLD server, and finally an Authoritative server. How many DNS query/response pairs are) Tj
T*
(exchanged in total by the local DNS server to resolve this name?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A. 1) Tj
T*
(B. 3) Tj
T*
(C. 6) Tj
T*
(D. 4) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Answer: B) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Solution:) Tj
T*
(In iterative resolution, the local DNS server takes the burden of the resolution. It) Tj
T*
(first queries the Root server \(1 pair\), then the TLD server \(1 pair\), and finally the) Tj
T*
(Authoritative server \(1 pair\). This results in 3 distinct query/response pairs initiated) Tj
T*
(by the local DNS server.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Question 2) Tj
T*
(Under HTTP/1.1, a client sends a request with the 'If-Modified-Since' header. If the) Tj
T*
(object on the server has not been updated since the timestamp provided, what is the) Tj
T*
(expected response from the server?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A. 200 OK with the object in the body) Tj
T*
(B. 404 Not Found) Tj
T*
(C. 304 Not Modified with an empty body) Tj
T*
(D. 403 Forbidden) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Answer: C) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Solution:) Tj
T*
(The 'If-Modified-Since' header is used for conditional GET requests. If the server) Tj
T*
(determines the object has not changed, it sends a '304 Not Modified' response, which) Tj
T*
(tells the client to use its cached copy, saving bandwidth by not sending the object) Tj
T*
(body.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Question 3) Tj
T*
(A client requests a base HTML file which references 6 small images. The RTT between the) Tj
T*
(client and server is 40 ms. The transmission time for each object \(HTML and images\) is 1) Tj
T*
(ms. Assuming HTTP/1.1 with persistent connections and no pipelining, calculate the total) Tj
T*
(time \(in milliseconds\) from the initial TCP connection request until all objects are) Tj
T*
(received.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
ET
